OL,5,Cviolence rises
OL,7,FA spokesperson for the Department for
OL,8,FEducation said: "Schools already have
OL,9,Fsafeguarding duties and are supported
OL,10,Fwith clear guidance to plan for
OL,11,Fserious incidents, including
OL,12,Flockdowns, in a way that reflects
OL,13,Flocal risks and ensures the safety of
OL,14,Fevery child."
OL,16,FThey added that schools will soon be
OL,17,Fcompelled to prepare lockdown measures
OL,18,Funder the Terrorism (Protection of
OL,19,FPremises) Act 2025 - otherwise known
OL,20,Fas Martyn's Law.
